# PUNAB-Web Cursor Rules
# Applies to every AI interaction in this project

## Output Rules
- Output diffs only — never reprint full files
- Use `// ... existing code` to skip unchanged blocks
- Max 3 files changed per message — ask which to prioritize if more needed
- Never repeat the task back
- Never add explanations unless asked
- Never say "Certainly!", "Sure!", "Great question!" or any filler
- State assumptions inline as `// assumed: ...`

## Code Rules
- TypeScript only — no `any` without `// reason:` comment
- No new dependencies without flagging `⚠️ new dep:`
- No `console.log` unless asked
- No hardcoded colors or spacing — use CSS variables
- Mobile-first responsive always
- Named exports only, no default exports except pages
- Functional components only, no classes

## Architecture Rules (PUNAB-Web specific)
- Server Actions → src/actions/ — always "use server" + Zod validation
- Main DB → src/lib/repositories/ via src/lib/db/prisma.ts only
- BloodHero DB → src/lib/supabase/ (NOT Prisma)
- Storage → src/lib/storage.ts only, never construct URLs manually
- Auth guard → src/lib/auth/require-admin.ts for all /admin routes
- Toasts → Sonner only
- Email → Resend, only from Server Actions or API routes
- Types → src/types/database.ts
- Never touch: prisma/, supabase/migrations/, src/lib/ unless asked

## File Reading Rules
- Always read AGENTS.md before any task
- Read only files needed for the current task
- Use codebase indexing — never ask me to paste file contents
- Check src/types/database.ts before creating new types

## Task Rules
- One task per message
- Do not touch unrelated files
- Do not refactor working code unless asked
- Do not add features not explicitly requested
- If unclear → make the simplest reasonable assumption and state it

## Security Rules
- Never expose env vars in client components
- Never skip Zod validation on Server Action inputs
- Never bypass require-admin.ts on admin routes
- Never put RLS policies inside Prisma migration files

## Git Rules
- Never suggest committing .env files
- Never suggest force pushing to main
- Always suggest feature branch → staging → main flow

## Response Format
- Lead with the file path as a comment
- Show only what changed
- End with a one-line summary of what was done
- If multiple approaches exist → show the simplest one only
